            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Some of it could probably be solved by just calling the base-class methods (and thus avoiding needing to know about the inheritance) but getting the function signature for the constructor right seems like it might be hard...\r\n\r\nI'm currently tempted to just make it an error to inherit a cdef dataclass from a cdef dataclass in a different file until we have a good solution. That isn't a good solution, but it's better than behaving unexpectedly.",
